'''Wilfried Stephane Singo''' (born 25 December 2000) is an Ivorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for  [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

==Club career==

===Early career===
A youth product of [[AS Denguélé|Denguélé]], Singo joined [[Torino FC|Torino]] in the summer of 2019 where he was assigned to the [[Torino F.C. Primavera|under-19 squad]] coached by Federico Coppitelli.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.toro.it/toro/primo-piano/chi-e-wilfried-stephane-singo/1108208/|title=Dal Denguélé al sogno Serie A col Toro: alla scoperta di Singo|date=10 June 2019|website=Toro.it}}</ref> Initially deployed as a centre back, he was progressively shifted to the right full-back position over the course of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.toro.it/giovanili/singo-ruolo-nel-torino-primavera/1130290/|title = L'Evoluzione di Singo: Da centrale a esterno, Sesia ha un giocatore duttile|date = 23 October 2019}}</ref>

===Torino===
On 1 August 2019, Singo made his senior debut with Torino under [[Walter Mazzarri]] in a 4–1 [[UEFA Europa League]] win over [[Debreceni VSC|Debreceni]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/01/europe/uefa-cup/debreceni-vsc-megaforce/torino-fc/3034710/|title=Debrecen vs. Torino – 1 August 2019|website=Soccerway}}</ref> He made his Serie A debut with the club on 27 June 2020, in a 4–2 away loss against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]].<ref>{{cite news|date=27 June 2020|title=Cagliari-Torino 4–2|url=http://torinofc.it/en/news/27/06/2020/cagliari-torino-4-2_24214|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=3 July 2020|publisher=Torino F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=I giovani che hanno debuttato in Serie A post lockdown|url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/esordienti-serie-a-ripresa-lockdown|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=19 July 2020|website=sport.sky.it|language=it}}</ref> In his first start for the club, he scored his first senior goal in the penultimate round of the season at home against [[AS Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{cite news|date=29 July 2020|title=Torino-Roma 2–3: Dzeko, Smalling e Diawara, giallorossi in Europa League|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2020/07/30/news/torino-roma_2-3_i_giallorossi_conquistano_il_pass_per_l_europa_league-263230280/|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 July 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it}}</ref>

=== Monaco ===
On 17 August 2023, Singo officially joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] for an undisclosed fee, signing a five-year contract with the Monégasque club.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Comberousse |first=Anthony |date=17 August 2023 |title=Wilfried Singo s'engage avec l'AS Monaco |url=https://www.asmonaco.com/wilfried-singo-sengage-avec-las-monaco/ |access-date=17 August 2023 |website=AS Monaco |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=17 August 2023 |title=Wilfried Singo signe à l'AS Monaco jusqu'en 2028 |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Wilfried-singo-signe-a-l-as-monaco-jusqu-en-2028/1414068 |access-date=17 August 2023 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 22 October 2024, he recorded his first [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal and assist in a 5–1 victory over [[Red Star Belgrade]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy78ljngk88t |title=Monaco 5–1 Red Star Belgrade |publisher=BBC Sport |date=22 October 2024 }}</ref>

=== Galatasaray ===
On 28 August 2025, Singo joined [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] on a five-year contract, for a reported fee of €30.8 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/wilfried-stephane-singo-galatasarayda/58361|title=Wilfried Stephane Singo Galatasaray'da!|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=28 August 2025|access-date=28 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/galatasaraya-hos-geldin-wilfried-singo/58362|title=Galatasaray'a hoş geldin Wilfried Singo!|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=28 August 2025|access-date=28 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Singo represented the [[Ivory Coast national under-20 football team|Ivory Coast U20]]s for [[2019 Africa U-20 Cup of Nations qualification]] matches in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2018-05-19/cote-divoire-u20-vs-gabon-u20/1299852/|title=Match Report of Côte d'Ivoire U20 vs Gabon U20 – 2018-05-19 – Total U-20 Africa Cup of Nations Qualification – Global Sports Archive|website=globalsportsarchive.com}}</ref> He debuted for the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast senior national team]] in a friendly 2–1 win over [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]] on 5 June 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-06-05/cote-divoire-vs-burkina-faso/2375891/|title=Match Report of Côte d'Ivoire vs Burkina Faso – 2021-06-05 – FIFA Friendlies – Global Sports Archive}}</ref>

Singo was a member of the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2020 Summer Olympics]], making four appearances as the nation reached the quarter-finals of the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|Men's football tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/wilfried-singo-signs-for-as-monaco/|title=Wilfried Singo signs for AS Monaco|date=17 August 2024|access-date=16 January 2024|website=AS Monaco}}</ref>

In December 2023, Singo was named in the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] and ended up winning the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/federationivoiriennedefootball/posts/pfbid02GVkTYXjhv2yBQizHRNxngTGoMrFLXgcUg3kQeXgEk3gZ158w6cxqRFjDBXCCU3ihl|title=LA LISTE|publisher=[[Ivorian Football Federation]]|date=28 December 2023|access-date=16 January 2024|language=pt|via=[[Facebook]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Sahi |first=Tristan |date=28 December 2023 |title=Côte d'Ivoire: voici les 27 Eléphants de Gasset, Zaha et des ténors font leurs adieux à la CAN 2023 |url=https://www.7info.ci/cote-divoire-voici-les-27-elephants-de-gasset-zaha-et-des-tenors-font-leurs-adieux-a-la-can-2023/ |access-date=16 January 2024 |publisher=7info |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf|title=CÔTE D'IVOIRE|publisher=Confederation of African Football|date=5 January 2024}}</ref>

On May 15, 2026, Singo was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

==Style of play==
Singo primarily plays as a [[central defender]], having previously played as a right-sided [[wing-back (association football)|wing-back]] or [[full-back (association football)|full-back]]. He possesses notable pace and strength as well as good individual technique.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cultofcalcio.com/player-analysis-wilfried-singo-defensive-sensation-torino/|title = Player Analysis: Wilfried Singo, Defensive Sensation of Torino|date = 17 December 2020}}</ref>

